[**Host Nun**](http://hostnun.net/congregation.html) was founded in July of 2013 after learning about the Vatican's offer of [**time off purgatory**](http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/jul/16/vatican-indulgences-pope-francis-tweets) to followers of Pope Francis's tweets. We have been providing shared and VPS hosting by way of various virtual cloisters ever since!

Our primary concern is with encouraging an 'ethics' of ascetic integrity throughout the hosting milieu, and with maintaining genuinely affordable prices as an inseperable aspect of that process. Whilst the traditional monastic rigours of poverty, chastity, and obedience remain vital to us, we are simultaneously interested in syncretistic approaches—i.e. _transgenesis_—to which we contrast the automatic failover systems of doctrinal isolationism.

This sale was originally submitted to Low End Box a couple weeks ago for our one year anniversary (July 31st). In the interim, the node that was reserved for it started gaining clients by other means, so we decided to make this thread instead, lest we reached capacity prior to the LEB mods getting a chance to consider it.

